title: Google\Cloud\Speech\V1\ListCustomClassesRequest
name: ListCustomClassesRequest
description:
Message sent by the client for the ListCustomClasses method.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.speech.v1.ListCustomClassesRequest

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The parent, which owns this collection of custom classes. Format: projects/{project}/locations/{location}/customClasses Speech-to-Text supports three locations: global, us (US North America), and eu (Europe). If you are calling the speech.googleapis.com endpoint, use the global location. To specify a region, use a regional endpoint with matching us or eu location value.

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: The maximum number of custom classes to return. The service may return fewer than this value. If unspecified, at most 50 custom classes will be returned. The maximum value is 1000; values above 1000 will be coerced to 1000.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: A page token, received from a previous ListCustomClass call. Provide this to retrieve the subsequent page. When paginating, all other parameters provided to ListCustomClass must match the call that provided the page token.
